Codifies the production SLOs (latency, availability, freshness) and
wires the Phase 5 SSE events into the existing alert webhook pipeline
so on-call is paged via PagerDuty/Slack like any other alert.

  - lib/slo/slo_definitions.ts        — 6 SLOs across critical/high/normal tiers
  - lib/slo/slo_tracker.ts            — observation ring buffer + burn rate calc
  - lib/alerts/sse_alert_router.ts    — Phase 5 events → fireAlert + SLO scanner
  - routes/slo.ts                     — /api/slo/{definitions,budgets,burn-rate,...}
  - load-tests/k6-scheduler-baseline.js — focused 20-VU 3min poll test
  - load-tests/k6-api-stress.js       — extended with scheduler + SLO endpoints
  - docs/SLOs.md                      — human-readable pair to slo_definitions

The SLO middleware is mounted in app.ts after the prometheus middleware
so it observes every /api/* request. The SSE alert router monkey-patches
the SignalStreamHub publish path to subscribe in-process — SSE clients
remain unaffected. Both subsystems are env-gated:

  SSE_ALERT_ROUTER_AUTOSTART  default true
  SLO_SCAN_INTERVAL_MS        default 60000
  SLO_OBSERVATION_MAX         default 5000

